# Wikipedia Data Extractor 

## Description
The automatic extraction of information in Wikipedia by using only regulars.

## What I used
- Python (Standard Library: `re`, `urllib.request`)

## Project
- `src/`: Codes.
- `docs/`: Report with 10 different cities.

## Results
The project extract succedly:
- Name of the city, Population, Area, Coordinates, Country, Altitud, TimeZone and Temprature(High, Low, Mean).

## How to run
1. Clone the repository.
2. Go to `src/`.
3. Run: `python main.py`
